ly recurses and doesn't short-circuit incorrectly.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.94,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"CONCATENATE joins values with separator and skips empty cells without inserting blanks","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Pure string manipulation logic. No I/O or external dependencies. The failure is in the concatenation algorithm (how empty cells are handled, separator application).","test_description":"Create cells: A1='hello', A2='' (empty), A3='world'. Create formula ==CONCATENATE(A1, A2, A3) or ==CONCATENATE(A1:A3). Verify result is 'helloworld' (not 'hello||world' or with extra separators). Test with multiple consecutive empty cells, numeric values, and special characters. Verify empty cells contribute nothing to output.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.94,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Formula references to cells in different sheets resolve correctly to the referenced value","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Cross-sheet reference resolution is in-memory logic (reference parsing and sheet lookup). Multiple sheets can coexist in memory without I/O. The failure is in reference parser or sheet lookup (does it parse 'Sheet2!A1' correctly? Does it find Sheet2?).","test_description":"Create Sheet2 with A1=5. In Sheet1, create cell with ==Sheet2!A1+1. Evaluate and verify result is 6. Test reference to non-existent sheet (verify error). Test various cell addresses (B10, Z100). Verify reference syntax is correctly parsed and sheet is correctly located.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"Changing a cell value triggers recalculation of all dependent formulas in correct topological order","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Tests the dependency-tracking and recalculation mechanism across multiple cells. A unit test of single evaluation wouldn't catch ordering bugs. The failure is at the state-change-propagation level: when A1 changes, B1 must recalculate before C1, and C1 must use B1's NEW value, not stale value.","test_description":"Create dependency chain: A1=5, B1==A1*2 (10), C1==B1+1 (11), D1==C1*2 (22). Change A1 to 10. Verify all cells recalculate to B1=20, C1=21, D1=42. Use internal inspection/logging to verify B1 recalculated before C1, C1 before D1 (topological order). Test changes at different points in the chain. Verify no cell uses stale upstream values.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Integration":0.75,"Unit":0.15,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"Undo operation restores both formula text and all dependent cell values after formula edit","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Undo requires managing snapshots of multiple cells (edited cell plus all dependents). A unit test of formula evaluation wouldn't verify whether dependent cells' saved state is properly restored. The failure is at the state-capture-and-restoration level.","test_description":"Set A1=5, B1==A1*2 (evaluates to 10). Edit B1 to ==A1*3. Verify B1 now evaluates to 15. Call undo(). Verify B1 contains original formula ==A1*2 and still evaluates to 10. Test with longer undo chains (multiple edits). Test with multiple dependent cells (B1 and C1 both depend on A1; edit A1; verify undo restores both).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Integration":0.82,"Unit":0.12,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"Saving and loading a workbook preserves all cell values, formulas, and floating-point precision with no data loss","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real filesystem I/O is required. Mocking file operations would hide serialization bugs, endianness issues, precision loss, and binary format errors. The failure boundary is at the OS level: did the bytes actually round-trip correctly?","test_description":"Create workbook with: integer cells, floating-point cells (including precision edge cases like 1.23456789), formula cells (=SUM, =VLOOKUP, =IF, cross-sheet refs), empty cells. Save to disk using engine's save(). Load using engine's load(). Verify: all cell values match exactly (including float bit patterns), all formulas are preserved as text, re-evaluating formulas produces identical results. Test floating-point edge cases (very large/small numbers, values near precision boundaries) to catch precision loss.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"System":0.85,"Integration":0.1,"Unit":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13658,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13658},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9b5c5223-e79b-498c-a2b4-1aecd80099c6","uuid":"4fe94daf-daa0-454e-a9b3-d88702ebfa3e"}
